    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1097"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1097">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/4048.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">German Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="90" xml:id="d1097fn90">Mutatis mutandis to the French and British
                        Embassies.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 996.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: The Secretary of the Navy has made known
                    to me information which he has received from the Commander-in-Chief <pb
                        facs="0799" n="683" xml:id="pg_683"/> of our Atlantic Fleet of the
                    assistance rendered by German naval vessels in removing American refugees from
                    Tampico to American men of war off the mouth of the river.</p>
                <p>It has given me pleasure to instruct the American Ambassador at Berlin to express
                    to your Government the cordial thanks of the Government of the United States for
                    this friendly service.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
